Anſwer. There could be no more good foreſeen in the Creature than what God did fore-ordain;
2 Tim. 1.9. therefore God choſe not 

      ••
   y for foreſeen good in them;
   Rom. 9.18. Matth. 20.15. Job 9.12.40.2. but he had Mercy on whom he would have Mercy, and whom he would he harden'd; and who may ſay to him what doeſt thou?

Anſwer, There is no difference beween the Elect and others by Nature,
   Rom. 3.9. Gal. 3.10 22.23, 24. and are alike the Children of Wrath, under Sin, ſhut up under the Law till Faith comes;
   Rom. 11.5, 6. 1 Cor. 4.7. Gal. 1.15.2.16.3.24. the difference is made only by Grace, which cauſeth the Elect in the time appointed to believe in Chriſt, that they may be juſtified by Faith in him.

Theſe Officers to be choſen by the Church from among themſelves, Acts 14.23. and by them to be ordain'd, or ſet a part to their
Work, with Faſting and Praying; without laying on of Hands;
Profit not. 1 Cor. 12.7. Edifie not. 1 Cor. 14.12, 26 that Ceremony being no more to be us'd, than waſhing of Feet, or anointing with Oyl; becauſe the glorious Gifts that once attended it, are long ſince ceas'd.

1ſt. Baptiſm
 for every Believer or Church-Member,
   Act. 2.39, 41. chap. 16.15, 33. Iſa. 44.3. Rev. 14.1. Matth. 28.19. with Iſa. 52.15. 1 Cor. 10.1.2. and their immediate infant-ſeed, by sprinkling or pouring Water only on the Face, in the Name of the Father, Son and Holy Spirit.
